<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 06 at 1:32PM MDT until July 06 at 2:00PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 200 PM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN JUDITH BASIN AND WEST CENTRAL FERGUS COUNTIES...
At 132 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Stanford,
moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Stanford, Denton, Coffee Creek, Windham and Benchland.
TORNADO...POSSIBLE
HAIL THREAT...OBSERVED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>This storm is producing large hail. SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy
structure and stay away from windows.</instruction>
